BOM:

BROWSER OBJECT MODEL: (U will talk to browser)

Window Object
Screen Object
Navigator Object
Location Object
History Object
Local Storage


Window Object:

it represents browser   window.

all js gloabal objects , (var ) function will be under     window.

ex: 

window.innerWidth
window.innerHeight

window ---> Screen Object:


availHeight
: 
1080
availLeft
: 
-1920
availTop
: 
-180
availWidth
: 
1920


window ---> Navigator Object:

brower setting information - 

like name of the browser , appname , cookieebaled or not


window -- Location Object:
url
path
host
https or not

History Object: handle the browser history:

History.back()

History.forward():


Local Storage & session storage:
way to store some information in the browser

Local: 
It keeps info forever untill u delete (either manually or using removeItem method)
localstorage.setItem(key,value)
localstorage.getItem(key)
localstorage.removeItem(key)

session
It keeps info only till u close the window 
sessionstorage.setItem(key,value)
sessionstorage.getItem(key)
sessionstorage.removeItem(key)



Cookie:
'How do remember if some connection loss happen'
or how i know about user information ?
Cookies are saved in name-value pairs like:
document.cookie='name=test;expires=Thu, 06 Jun 2023 20:59:00'